<Content>Lovely hotel, but don't order the duck! A wonderful boutique hotel in a super area in Boston. Rooms are a bit small, and slightly noisy at times (from the street), but it is a fantastic place to stay for location and service. It has an excellent restaurant attached, which provides an extensive breakfast menu (included in room charge). Evening menu is great, seems to be well subscribed to by local residents. But don't order the duck - it's a bit anaemic, leading to a rather bland dining experience - though other meals, chicken/steak/fish are much better( based on one meal experience only!) Would definitely stay here again. (Also has free internet access........!) 
