<Author>Eric001
<Content>Excellent Hotel We stayed for one night on our way to Martha's Vineyard. We've been to Boston before so didn't feel the need to stay longer (had a fabulous meal at Bricco's in North End!). We stayed in one of the Queen rooms. The room wasn't that big but made good use of space (ironing board folds out from cupboard, LCD TV on wall) and most importantly was clean, although the carpet was beginning to show signs of age. The bathroom was spotless and well equipped (a real plus for my wife!). What we really loved was the character of the room. We've stayed at hotels twice the price and they are just modern and sterile. The downstairs bar was small and inviting with good range of wines, beers and spirits considering it's size. All the staff were helpful, courteous, efficient, and friendly (unfortunately often a rarity these days). Nothing was too much trouble. We enjoyed our stay so much we are cutting our Vineyard trip by 1 day to return for a last night in Boston before returning to the UK. 
