<Author>karynd
<Content>Great place We loved the location on Beacon Hill which is right in the middle of everything. The hotel is small and we got to know all the staff within the few days we were there. Benson (the manager) was very knowledgeable about the city and helped get us great restaurant reservations. The rooms are not big but we didn't care since we were there to walk around the city. The sitting room on the second floor and the third floor terrace gave us the extra space we needed to relax. The bar was great with many locals and Chelsea (the bartender) was fun to talk to. We would definitely stay here if we come back to Boston 
